    {
        "content": "<p>In ordinary mathematics, you can't really distinguish <code>‚ä§ : submodule K E</code> from <code>E</code> itself. But <code>‚ä§</code> is the module viewed as submodule of itself.</p>",
        "id": 317037580,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1671569430
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Nowadays I frequently catch myself saying things like \"E seen as a submodule of itself\" in lectures...</p>",
