    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110031\">Patrick Massot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Trying.20to.20prove.3A.20any.20strict.20subspace.20has.20empty.20interior/near/317037258\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You can write <code>interior (F : set E) = ‚àÖ</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>that does work, but then I run into <a href=\"#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/Taking.20element.20from.20non-empty.20set/near/316731842\">this issue</a> again (I'm starting the proof with the <code>contrapose</code> and <code>assume</code> tactics, then I think I need to apply the <code>cases</code> tactic in order to get an element from the (assumed) non-empty interior without using the axiom of choice, but I can't really figure out a way from <code>¬¨interior ‚ÜëF = ‚àÖ</code> to <code>(interior F).nonempty</code>)</p>",
